There is not a clear date on the document and there is no agreement between HdH and JP. There is also no clear agreement on where this ship stopped in Africa (Henk says Elmina, Postmas says Loanda-Angola, SV says Congo North). Since I don't really understand what is meant by Congo North, and since at this time many slave ships were going to Angola, I am going to go with Postma. Perhaps documents will reveal something else as we continue.

column55: Arch doc says Ardra, which was the name used to refer to the current town of Allada. Ardra was the capital of the Fon kingdom (also called Allada) until it fell to Dahomey in 1724). SV uses Ouidah, which is the city on the coast; Allada in 34 kilometers inland.
